name: GA AG Chris Carr
tweet: HOLIDAY SHOPPING TIP (thread): And remember, if you actually do miss a shipment, the delivery company generally leaves a notice on your door or in your mailbox.   More ->  https://t.co/hxiD2vauZJ  https://t.co/Zub5D8u2Ni

name: GA AG Chris Carr
tweet: HOLIDAY SHOPPING TIP (thread): Avoid clicking on these links or downloading any attachments. If you need to track a package, the safest thing to do is to pull up your order confirmation and use the links or phone number provided there.   More ->  https://t.co/hxiD2vauZJ  https://t.co/QWsitADGlu

name: GA AG Chris Carr
tweet: HOLIDAY SHOPPING TIP (thread): Sometimes these messages include a link or file attachment, which could download malware onto your device. Other times, the scammer is trying to steal your money or trick you into providing personal information.  More ->  https://t.co/hxiD2vauZJ  https://t.co/zl64TbfcxE

name: GA AG Chris Carr
tweet: HOLIDAY SHOPPING TIP (thread): Scammers may send you a text or email that purports to come from @amazon, @USPS, @UPS or @FedEx saying that you missed a delivery or there’s an update about your package or account.   More ->  https://t.co/hxiD2vauZJ  https://t.co/Lja7QsxaOc

tweet: 2/2: US Attorney Peeler will leave the @USAO_MDGA in a safer and more prosperous state, and he will be missed as he returns to private practice. We thank him greatly for his service these past three years.

name: GA AG Chris Carr
tweet: ‼️ If you receive a message about participating in a trial, don’t click the link, give out your SSN or provide financial info. If you are asked to provide your bank account so you can receive payment for your participation, ask them to mail you a check.   https://t.co/RIJUaZLK8V

name: GA AG Chris Carr
tweet: ‼️ The message they send may contain a link that downloads malware, enabling them to steal the account numbers and passwords stored on your device. Remember, real clinical trials will never ask you to pay them.   https://t.co/RIJUaZLK8V

name: GA AG Chris Carr
tweet: ‼️ Scam artists are creating fake websites and promotional messages in which they offer to pay you $1,000 or more for participating in a #COVID19 vaccine trial. They may ask you for your SSN, bank account information or credit card information.   https://t.co/RIJUaZLK8V
